AN ACT relating to motor vehicles; requiring the Department of Motor Vehicles,
under certain circumstances, to issue a special license plate [to a
veteran of the Space Force;] honoring certain veterans; authorizing
the combination of personalized prestige license plates and certain
special license plates associated with military service; and providing
other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the Department of Motor Vehicles to issue personalized prestige
2 license plates and certain special license plates associated with military or public service.
3 (NRS 482.3667, 482.3757-482.3787)
4 Existing law requires the Department to issue special license plates for the support of
5 outreach programs and services for veterans and their families to: (1) a veteran of the Army,
6 Navy, Air Force, Marine Corps or Coast Guard of the United States, a reserve component
7 thereof or the National Guard; (2) a female veteran; or (3) the spouse, parent or child of a
8 veteran or female veteran. Existing law requires the plates to be inscribed with the seal of the
9 branch of the Armed Forces, the seal of the National Guard or an image representative of
10 female veterans, as applicable. (NRS 482.3763) Section 1 of this bill requires the issuance,
11 upon application, of such special license plates to veterans of the Space Force and the spouse,
12 parent or child of such veterans.
13 Existing law requires the Department to issue special license plates honoring
14 veterans of the Armed Forces of the United States who have been awarded the: (1) Silver
15 Star; or (2) Bronze Star Medal with “V” device, Combat V or Combat Distinguishing
16 Device. (NRS 482.3783) Section 1.5 of this bill requires the Department to issue special
17 license plates honoring veterans who have been awarded the: (1) Air Force Cross; (2)
18 Coast Guard Cross; (3) Distinguished Service Cross; or (4) Navy Cross.
19 Existing law requires the Department to issue, upon application, a special license plate to
20 each family member of a person: (1) killed in the line of duty while on active duty in the
21 Armed Forces of the United States; or (2) who died as a result of injuries sustained while on
22 active duty in the Armed Forces of the United States. (NRS 482.3785, 482.3787) Sections 2
23 and 3 of this bill authorize a person to request that personalized prestige license plates be
24 combined with such special license plates.

